But what about businesses - don't they make most of the garbage?

It's true - altogether we produce about twice as much waste outside of our homes, at the places where we work, shop, go to school, play or are cared for, such as in hospital.
Don't forget - it's us who work at those businesses too. Whether at home or at work, we must do whatever possible to prevent needless waste.
Business waste is an area that City Council is aggressively purusing towards waste reduction, with policies etc.
We need to be responsible for doing our part at home as well.

We may not see the costs of filling up our landfill on our bill every month, but we do pay a lot to operate and continually expand our landfill. Eventually future generations will pay to repair the damage to our environment.

From the City of Lethbridge:

"The area currently permitted for landfill is approaching capacity. At current disposal rates it is estimated that there is between 12 and 15 years of capacity available. The City has additional land adjacent to the centre and will be seeking approval from Alberta Environment to expand the landfill's permitted area (or footprint) as well as the maximum height for waste placement."
